@jorgheymans This supercedes https://github.com/openzipkin/zipkin/pull/2822

Fixes #2824

Whenever I did JMH stuff, I kept updated the benchmark and improved the
code, later reverting the main code and running again. I often chose to
combine multiple small improvements in the same PR. I noticed others
due so too.

Anyway, @Logic-32 has questioned if changes made things worse despite me
pasting in before and after runs using JRE 11 (which is what our docker
image uses).

This change makes it easier for someone else to run the same benchmark
file against older commits so that any further improvements can be
assessed independently all the way back to vs the last release.

For example with the below diff you can run against the tag 2.15.0.

```diff
diff --git a/benchmarks/src/main/java/zipkin2/server/internal/throttle/ThrottledCallBenchmarks.java b/benchmarks/src/main/java/zipkin2/server/internal/throttle/ThrottledCallBenchmarks.java
index 5e9ce58be..8d05230f0 100644
--- a/benchmarks/src/main/java/zipkin2/server/internal/throttle/ThrottledCallBenchmarks.java
+++ b/benchmarks/src/main/java/zipkin2/server/internal/throttle/ThrottledCallBenchmarks.java
@@ -13,7 +13,6 @@
  */
 package zipkin2.server.internal.throttle;

-import com.linecorp.armeria.common.metric.NoopMeterRegistry;
 import com.netflix.concurrency.limits.limit.FixedLimit;
